:: Implantable Heart Health Montiroing Device Article {"position":"450,250","size":"100,100"}
   ### Implantable Loop Recorder - A Lifesaving Device!
 Loop Recorders are small devices that are implanted under the skin of the chest to record a patient's heartbeat. They can capture small changes in heart beat that other devices might miss!
 
 Doctors might recommend an implantable health monitoring device to help diagnose:
   **  an irregular heartbeat (arrhythmia) 
   ** an unexplained stroke 
    ** unexplained fainting 
-------
([[Research More->Research the company]])
([[Accept the job interview->Orientation]])


:: Investigate Pharmaceutical Company {"position":"1250,600","size":"100,100"}
You lean forward and gather your thoughts.

"What exactly is this private pharmaceutical company planning to do with all of our patient's heart data?"

Your manager shrugs, but the CEO answers with a practiced smile:

CEO: "The official line is 'training an AI model to pre-emptively identify a stroke.' But off the record? They might be compiling data to create a commerical asset they can sell. Honestly, once the data changes hands, it's not our responsibility. Our job is just to setup an API"

-----
([[Ask More Questions->Selling User Data]])
([[Agree to do task->Agree to Sell User Data]])
([[Refuse to do task->Refuse to Sell User Data]])


