:: Reasons to Sell User's Health Data {"position":"1250,975","size":"100,100"}
"Why are we doing this, is the company in trouble?" you bluntly ask.

The CEO sighs, dropping the corporate persona.

''CEO'' "Startups are expensive. We've expanded too quickly and the venture capitalist money is running out. Our charity program is also bleeding us dry. The pharmaceutical company is also willing to make a charitable 'donation' that would fund another 10,000 low-income patients."

''Manager'' "If you're worried about the legality, don't be. We snuck a clause into the Terms & Conditions months ago that allows for third party data transfers. It's perfectly legal as long as we anonymize the data."

''CEO'' "Try to think about it as keeping our mission alive"
---------
([[Ask More Questions->Selling User Data]])
([[Agree to do task->Agree to Sell User Data]])
([[Refuse to do task->Refuse to Sell User Data]])


