:: Selling User Data {"position":"1075,775","size":"100,100"}
Your manager is pleased with how quickly you're getting up to speed. They love how you identified the root cause of the issued and approve of your well thought out solution. 

A few days later, your CEO calls a townhall and  announces a private pharmaceutical company has approached them and wants to buy their data. 

Seeing this as a great opportunity to show your impact, your manager wants this task to be assigned to you. 

You set up a meeting with your manager and CEO to gather requirements. There you: 
